UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2615
1 A RESOLUTION affirming the supremacy of United States and Kentucky law over
2 foreign law.
3 WHEREAS, the threat posed by terrorism has been well established both beyond
4 and within the borders of the United States and this Commonwealth; and
5 WHEREAS, the threat of terrorism within the homeland is primarily the result of a
6 legal-political-military doctrine combined with Islamic religious beliefs known as Sharia,
7 a system adhered to or advocated by millions of its followers around the world; and
8 WHEREAS, Sharia as a political doctrine requires its adherents to actively support
9 the establishment of a political society based upon Sharia as foundational or supreme law
10 and the replacement of any political entity not governed by Sharia with a Sharia political
11 order; and
12 WHEREAS, Sharia includes a doctrine of armed conflict, often referred to as jihad,
13 which has been considered by many scholars across historical periods as a significant
14 component of its legal and traditional framework; and
15 WHEREAS, many interpretations of jihad frame its ultimate objective as the
16 expansion or establishment of governance aligned with Islam through Sharia law across
17 states and societies, invoking coercive or unlawful actions to impose and institute Sharia;
18 and
19 WHEREAS, the institution of Sharia would require the destruction, abrogation, or
20 violation of the Constitution of the United States and the Constitution of Kentucky; and
21 WHEREAS, the threat from Sharia-based jihad and terrorism presents a real and
22 present danger to the lawful governance of this Commonwealth and to the peaceful
23 enjoyment of citizenship by its residents;
24 NOW, THEREFORE,
25 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
26 Kentucky:
27 Section 1. The Senate affirms that the Constitution of the United States and the
