1 Constitution of Kentucky are and shall remain the supreme law in this Commonwealth,
2 and no foreign law or legal system, including Sharia, may interfere with or undermine the
3 rights or protections enshrined in those documents.
4 Section 2. The Senate condemns any foreign law or legal system that runs
5 contrary to the supreme laws of this Commonwealth and declares that this honorable
6 body will take any necessary action to safeguard constitutional protections for all
7 Kentuckians.
